Class MojmirAutomaton.State<R,S>

  • Object
    • ltl2rabin.Automaton.State<R,S>
      • ltl2rabin.MojmirAutomaton.State<R,S>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - The type of the a State's label
    S - The letter format
    Enclosing class:
    MojmirAutomaton<T,L>

    public static class MojmirAutomaton.State<R,S>
extends Automaton.State<R,S>
    A MojmirAutomaton.State additionaly to a Automaton.State has a flag indicating if it is a sink or not.

    A MojmirAutomaton.State can be accepting or not, depending on a set of G-formulas that are assumed to hold. To check whether a state is accepting or not, call its isAcceptingState(Set) method.

    See Also:
    Automaton.State

      • isSink

        public boolean isSink()
        A State is a sink, if all outgoing transitions are self loops.

        Note: This method might return wrong results, if the construction of the MojmirAutomaton containing this state is not finished yet. It only is safe to call if this State is in a MojmirAutomaton that has been constructed by a MojmirAutomatonFactory.

        Returns:
        True, if the State is a sink. False, otherwise.

      • isAcceptingState

        public boolean isAcceptingState(Set<G> curlyG)
        A state is accepting, if, for a given set of G formulas curlyG, the conjunct of this set implies the formula the state is labelled with.
        Parameters:
        curlyG - A set of formulas of type G
        Returns:
        True, if the state is accepting for curlyG. False otherwise.

      • readLetter

        public MojmirAutomaton.State<R,S> readLetter(S letter)
        Description copied from class: Automaton.State
        Return the State of same type that is reached after "reading" a letter (usually this is formally denoted by δ(q, ν).

        Every State has outgoing transitions. A transition maps a letter to a State. How the transitions are stored depends on the implementation of Automaton.State and Automaton.

        Note: Since the base class only describes deterministic automata the transitions are deterministic.

        Specified by:
        readLetter in class Automaton.State<R,S>
        Parameters:
        letter - The letter (ν) that is consumed by the transition
        Returns:
        The state the transition maps to.
        See Also:
        Automaton.State.readLetter(Object)
